  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Capture the problem and a possible solution in as a business model in minimalistic and flexible manner using Business&#xD;
    Model Canvas.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe problem and corresponding customer segments&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe Unique Value Proposition. The UVP should state why you are different and worth buying&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe top features of solution&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe paths to customers&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe cost structure and revenue streams&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe key metrics and activities you measure&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe unfair advantage,&amp;nbsp;why the solution cannot be easily copied or bought&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    (Source: Maruya 2012, p. 45)&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>Capture business model hypotheses.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
